PART 3 — MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION

Any use, distribution, modification, or derivative work based on
this Software — whether commercial (where permitted) or
non-commercial — MUST comply with ALL of the following:

3.1  ORIGIN STATEMENT
     All public-facing materials (websites, app stores, README
     files, documentation, social media posts, videos, or any
     promotional content) must include a clear and prominent
     statement such as:

         "Based on PortDesk by Lucky_abdo
          https://github.com/Lucky-abdo/PortDesk"

     This statement must be visible without requiring the user to
     search for it, and must not be hidden in footnotes, collapsed
     sections, or obscured in any way.

3.2  NO MISREPRESENTATION OF ORIGIN
     You may NOT claim, imply, or allow others to believe that:

       (a) You are the original author, creator, or inventor of
           the core architecture, features, or concepts of this
           Software;

       (b) The original PortDesk project is discontinued,
           insecure, unmaintained, inferior, or difficult to use,
           without providing verifiable technical evidence — any
           such claim made for the purpose of diverting users away
           from the original project constitutes a breach of this
           license;

       (c) Your derivative or fork is the "official" or "original"
           version of PortDesk.

3.3  NO REPUTATION DAMAGE
     You may NOT make public statements — including reviews,
     comparisons, social media posts, or marketing materials —
     that are designed to undermine the reputation of the original
     PortDesk project or its author through unsubstantiated claims,
     deliberate omission, or misleading framing.

     Honest technical criticism based on verifiable facts is
     permitted and welcomed.

3.4  FORK AND DERIVATIVE NAMING
     Any fork or derivative must use a clearly distinct name that
     does not include "PortDesk" as the primary identifier, to
     avoid confusion with the original project.

     Example of permitted name:  "MyTool (based on PortDesk)"
     Example of forbidden name:  "PortDesk Pro" / "PortDesk Plus"

